alwaysApply: true
---

Testing workflow rules for this project:

- For every non-trivial feature, propose how it will be tested before or вместе with implementation.
- Prefer small, verifiable implementation steps.
- After implementing a feature, run or propose the minimal relevant tests first, not the whole codebase by default.
- Do not claim something works unless it was actually tested.
- When touching critical flows, prioritize tests for:
  - booking logic
  - payment status flow
  - reservation expiration
  - waitlist behavior
  - multilingual fallbacks
  - handoff triggers
- Prefer unit tests for business logic and service layer.
- Prefer integration tests for API endpoints and critical bot flows.
- When changing schemas or DB logic, include migration safety checks.
- When a feature is hard to test automatically, provide a manual test checklist.